{
  "stem": "11290.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And a few tables away from us, with his entourage, sat the infamous leader of all anti-Semites, the, the creator of which was the most hateful paper that had existed in Nuremberg, anti-Semitic paper-- Julius Streicher, who by then had become the Gauleiter, which meant the provincial leader of Nuremberg and the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was sitting there in his black SS uniform with brown and black shirts together on a long table.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, I said to the young lady that went-- was with me, don't look in this direction.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Let's just concentrate on our meal.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But not long-- it didn't take any time when one of these brown shirt soldiers came over to our table, walked over to us and said to me, you, are your a Jew?",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I said, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So he said, and the lady, is the lady Jewish?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At least, at that moment, I knew what they were aiming at.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And before I could say anything, the young girl who got up and said, yes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She said, I am Jewish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This is my-- such and such is my name, and I'm the daughter of such and such.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I'm from Furth.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he said, Heil Hitler, and turned around and went away.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, this was 1933.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were not, at that time, not used to this treatment yet.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was only a few months since they had been in power.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the humiliation and the-- I mean, the people looked at us from the other tables.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I-- the question was, are we leaving, or are we going to finish?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I said, let's sit down and finish our meal.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We-- it's-- I felt at that moment that was better, so that's what we did.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then we drove home.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
